Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art on rock face, showing pecked, infilled figures of five Nile river boats. That at bottom left is clearest, with 10 oars and ostrich-like figure with extra protuberance at neck above, upright and facing left. Above this is another with oars pointing up, above this two further, similar and more schematic. To lower right another, similar, cut off edge of image at right. Below this boat is schematic figure of cow with horns intersecting with boat, infilled with scattered pecking, upright and facing left. Above this boat is unidentified shape (another boat, long?) above this boat are two unidentified shapes also cut off. El-Kanais, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
